26 LC 112 4299
House Resolution 50EX
By: Representatives Reeves of the 99th, Hong of the 103rd, Clark of the 100th, Martinez of the
111th, and Donatucci of the 105th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing September 2026 as World OKTA Global Startup Month; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, World OKTA has faithfully contributed to the advancement of global
4 commerce, entrepreneurship, economic cooperation, and the strengthening of international
5 business networks among Korean entrepreneurs around the world; and
6 WHEREAS, the organization has encouraged innovation and startup development by
7 supporting emerging entrepreneurs, small businesses, and next-generation leaders through
8 mentorship, investment opportunities, education, and international collaboration; and
9 WHEREAS, the celebration of "World OKTA Global Startup Month" recognizes the
10 significant economic, cultural, and community contributions made by Korean-owned
11 businesses and startup leaders throughout the global marketplace; and
12 WHEREAS, fostering entrepreneurship and startup innovation creates opportunities for
13 economic growth, job creation, cross-cultural partnership, and future leadership development
14 within local and international communities; and
H. R. 50EX
- 1 -

26 LC 112 4299
15 WHEREAS, it is fitting and proper to honor the dedication, vision, and accomplishments of
16 World OKTA members and startup entrepreneurs who continue to build bridges of
17 cooperation and prosperity across nations.
18 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
19 the members of this body recognize September 2026 as World OKTA Global Startup Month
20 in honor of the positive impact of the entrepreneurship, innovation, and global partnership
21 fostered through the efforts of World OKTA.
22 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
23 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the
24 public and the press.
